      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROLL TO THE TOP (8) turned in a strong performance last start when she came from this row to just miss out by a nose at Parkes. Good winner at Wagga three back and races very well at this circuit and distance with two wins and a placing from four attempts. MILLWOOD GRACE NZ (10) has improved with each start this time in, culminating in a win last time out by 2.3 metres at Temora. Hard to know where she gets to from this slightly awkward draw but with even luck she could go on with it. JEWEL MISTRESS (9) has produced some decent efforts since she came from this barrier to win at Parkes last month. Contender. A low draw could see DANCE BABY DANCE (2) add to a series of top-four finishes.",
